'''阿拉瓦利'''（ Aravalli district）为[[印度|印度]][[古吉拉特邦|古吉拉特邦]]县份之一，2013年8月15日自[[萨巴坎塔县|萨巴坎塔]]（Sabarkantha）析置，因阿拉瓦利山脉（[[:en:Aravalli_Range|Aravalli Range]]）得名<ref>{{cite news|title=Aravalli now a district in Gujarat|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_aravalli-now-a-district-in-gujarat_1742376|accessdate=23 February 2013|newspaper=DNA|date=18 September 2012|archive-date=2012-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028135542/http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_aravalli-now-a-district-in-gujarat_1742376|dead-url=no}}</ref>。阿拉瓦利县现有676个自然村和306村务委员会（潘查亚特），人口有102万（2013年）<ref name=modi/>，[[行政中心|行政中心]]为[[莫达萨市|莫达萨市]]（[[:en:Modasa|Modasa]]）。

== 历史 ==
阿拉瓦利县是古吉拉特邦2013年新设的7个县份之一<ref>{{cite news|title=Seven new districts to be formed in Gujarat|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/GUJ-AHD-seven-new-districts-to-be-formed-in-gujarat-4158081-NOR.html|accessdate=23 February 2013|newspaper=Daily Bhaskar|date=January 24, 2013|archive-date=2013-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927123407/http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/GUJ-AHD-seven-new-districts-to-be-formed-in-gujarat-4158081-NOR.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2013年自萨巴坎塔划出莫达萨、马尔普尔（Malpur）、丹苏拉（Dhansura）、梅格拉杰（Meghraj）、碧罗达（Bhiloda）和巴雅特（Bayad）6个乡设置<ref name=modi>{{cite news|first=Kapil|last=Dave|title=Dignity of PM office has reached its nadir: Modi|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/city/ahmedabad/Dignity-of-PM-office-has-reached-its-nadir-Modi/articleshow/22064574.cms|accessdate=26 August 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|date=August 25, 2013|archive-date=2014-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508235129/http://m.timesofindia.com/city/ahmedabad/Dignity-of-PM-office-has-reached-its-nadir-Modi/articleshow/22064574.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其中马尔普尔、梅格拉杰和碧罗达三乡人员构成以部落为基础<ref name="indianexpress">{{cite news|title=Namesake of oldest mountain, Aravalli scores nil in industry|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/namesake-of-oldest-mountain-aravalli-scores-nil-in-industry/1163303/0|accessdate=23 September 2013|newspaper=The Indian Express|date=2 September 2013}}</ref>。
